lat-124012900522_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgail-q3-results-net-profit-up-10-fold-at-rs-2-843-cr-revenue-remains-flat-124012900522_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgail-q3-results-net-profit-up-10-fold-at-rs-2-843-cr-revenue-remains-flat-124012900522_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20conservative%20fix%20for%20the%20housing%20crisis%20is%20making%20homes%20cheaper%20and%20more%20abundant%20in%20Texas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Townhouses%20and%20homes%20in%20Houston's%20Montrose%20neighborhood%20Monday%2C%20March%2028%2C%202016%2C%20in%20Houston.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b14ea543bb77284ba03b2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENewer%20townhouses%20next%20to%20older%20homes%20in%20Houston's%20Montrose%20neighborhood%20in%20Houston%20in%202016.%3Cp%3EJames%20Nielsen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHouston%20has%20pioneered%20a%20key%20land-use%20policy%20reform%20that%20has%20helped%20create%20abundant%20starter%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Texas%20city%20shrunk%20the%20required%20lot%20size%20for%20a%20single-family%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20change%20has%20created%2080%2C000%20new%20homes%20without%20inflating%20land%20values.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%2C%20Texas%20is%20known%20for%20its%20Space%20Center%20and%20bayous%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%2C%20more%20recently%2C%20its%20abundant%20starter%20homes.%20Houston's%20newer%20townhomes%20built%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20decades%20join%20the%20brownstones%20of%20New%20York%20City%2C%20the%20rowhouses%20of%20DC%2C%20and%20the%20Victorians%20of%20San%20Francisco%20as%20a%20form%20of%20relatively%20dense%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20unlike%20its%20coastal%20counterparts%2C%20Houston's%20homes%20are%20much%20cheaper%20and%20more%20abundant.%20The%20city%20is%20building%20lots%20of%20what%20most%20of%20the%20country%20desperately%20needs%3A%20affordable%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKey%20to%20this%20is%20Houston's%20approach%20to%20an%20influential%2C%20but%20little-known%20land-use%20policy%3A%20minimum%20lot%20sizes.%20Since%20the%20early%20to%20mid-20th%20century%2C%20virtually%20all%20American%20cities%20have%20imposed%20rules%20that%20require%20single-family%20homes%20to%20sit%20on%20at%20least%205%2C000%20to%2010%2C000%20square%20feet%20of%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20rural%20areas%20with%20limited%20water%20and%20sewer%20infrastructure%2C%20low-density%20living%20makes%20sense%20as%20a%20health%20and%20practical%20matter.%20But%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20requiring%20large%20lots%20only%20makes%20neighborhoods%20more%20exclusive%20and%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20a%20way%20to%20limit%20housing%20construction%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Emily%20Hamilton%2C%20a%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20Mercatus%20Center%20at%20George%20Mason%20University.%20She%20added%20that%20minimum%20lot%20sizes%20maintain%20%26quot%3Ba%20homogenous%20type%20of%20housing%20construction%20with%20often%20a%20high%20floor%20on%20how%20expensive%20it%20has%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERestricting%20construction%20encourages%20sprawl%2C%20which%20makes%20walking%20anywhere%20difficult%20and%20driving%20necessary.%20Minimum%20lot%20sizes%20make%20homes%20an%20average%20of%20about%20%2430%2C000%20more%20expensive%20than%20those%20in%20similar%2C%20less%20regulated%20areas%2C%20and%20reduce%20density%20by%2011%25%2C%20housing%20researchers%20Joseph%20Gyourko%20and%20Sean%20McCulloch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw31710%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20urban%20housing%20in%20demand%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20city%20leaders%20decided%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%20In%201998%2C%20Houston%20shrunk%20its%20single-family%20lot%20size%20requirement%20from%205%2C000%20square%20feet%20to%201%2C400%20square%20feet%20in%20most%20of%20the%20city.%20In%202013%2C%20the%20city%20expanded%20that%20policy%20to%20all%20land%20that%20receives%20its%20wastewater%20collection%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%20have%20been%20dramatic.%20The%20policy%20change%20has%20spurred%20the%20construction%20of%20almost%2080%2C000%20new%20homes%2C%20many%20of%20them%20townhouses%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20small-lot%20single-family%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20unlike%20some%20other%20upzoning%20measures%2C%20Houston's%202013%20reforms%20didn't%20push%20land%20values%20up%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fworking-papers%2Feffects-minimum-lot-size-reform-houston-land-values%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHamilton%20found%20in%20a%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20earlier%20this%20month.%20She%20and%20other%20researchers%20believe%20this%20is%20because%20the%20land-use%20change%20applies%20to%20such%20a%20large%20geographic%20area.%20When%20development%20capacity%20increases%20on%20so%20many%20lots%20and%20spurs%20lots%20of%20new%20construction%20across%20the%20city%2C%20the%20expected%20income%20from%20any%20one%20piece%20of%20land%20is%20diminished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamilton%20said%20her%20findings%20were%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20some%20other%20upzoning%20efforts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyonahfreemark.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2FFreemark-Upzoning-Chicago.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20been%20shown%20to%20increase%20land%20values%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20counteracting%20some%20of%20the%20affordability%20benefits%20of%20allowing%20for%20more%20housing.%20But%20what%20sets%20Houston%20apart%20is%20that%20the%20policy%20change%20spurred%20lots%20of%20new%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20probably%20the%20most%20radical%20land-use%20reform%20adopted%20by%20any%20US%20city%20over%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20certainly%20the%20most%20successful%20by%20unit%20count%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nolan%20Gray%2C%20a%20city%20planner%20and%20research%20director%20for%20California%20YIMBY%20who's%20done%20research%20on%20Houston's%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20townhome%20is%20shown%20for%20sale%20on%20Freund%20St.%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20April%2013%2C%202022%20in%20Houston.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cd2f928df5080019d31243%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20townhome%20is%20shown%20for%20sale%20on%20Freund%20St.%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20April%2013%2C%202022%20in%20Houston.%3Cp%3EBrett%20Coomer%2FHouston%20Chronicle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20'free%20lunch%20opportunity'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShrinking%20or%20eliminating%20minimum%20lot%20sizes%20may%20be%20radical%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20kind%20of%20market-based%20approach%20that%20pro-housing%20advocates%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20support.%20Many%20conservatives%20are%20joining%20progressives%20in%20pushing%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20many%20regulations%20that%20limit%20housing%20density.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston's%20lot%20size%20reform%20would%20make%20sense%20all%20over%20the%20country.%20While%20some%20Americans%20still%20want%20picket%20fences%20and%20far-flung%20subdivisions%2C%20dense%20and%20walkable%20neighborhoods%20are%20more%20desirable%20these%20days.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartgrowthamerica.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FFoot-Traffic-Ahead-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanalysis%20published%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20homebuyers%20in%20the%2035%20biggest%20American%20metropolitan%20areas%20paid%2034%25%20more%20to%20live%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20while%20renters%20paid%2041%25%20more.%20Minimum%20lot%20sizes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0on%20top%20of%20other%20restrictive%20land-use%20policies%20like%20single-family%20zoning%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0make%20these%20walkable%20communities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-housing-prices-shortage-apartment-rent-zoning-policies-support-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegal%20to%20build%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20essentially%20mandating%20the%20most%20environmentally%20unfriendly%20pattern%20of%20living%20and%20in%20a%20context%20where%20many%20millions%20of%20Americans%2C%20if%20prices%20are%20any%20indication%2C%20want%20to%20live%20a%20different%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston's%20reform%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frice.app.box.com%2Fs%2F913lhxudorqkkzqottburrhh51flrr3d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimited%20gentrification%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2C%20instead%2C%20encouraged%20new%20construction%20in%20higher-income%20neighborhoods%2C%20which%20are%20exactly%20the%20kinds%20of%20places%20that%20tend%20to%20welcome%20the%20fewest%20new%20residents%20in%20most%20cities.%20And%20the%20more%20affordable%20homes%20that%20come%20online%2C%20the%20more%20possible%20it%20is%20for%20Black%2C%20brown%2C%20and%20other%20marginalized%20communities%20to%20own%20homes%20and%20shrink%20the%20racial%20wealth%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Houston%20has%20very%20few%20zoning%20laws%20in%20place%20at%20all%2C%20homes%20can%20be%20built%20on%20property%20that%20used%20to%20house%20commercial%20or%20industrial%20buildings.%20%26quot%3BThose%20new%20townhouses%20outside%20of%20I-610%20are%20often%20replacing%20dead%20strip%20malls%20or%20self-storage%20or%20other%20relatively%20low-value%20commercial%20uses%2C%20rather%20than%20single-family%20houses%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamilton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGray%20thinks%20Houston's%20success%20with%20smaller%20lot%20sizes%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20city's%20%26quot%3Bpro-growth%20culture.%26quot%3B%20That%20culture%20of%20deregulation%20also%20has%20downsides.%20The%20city%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftcwp.tamu.edu%2Ffiles%2F2015%2F06%2FWetlandLossPub.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20paved%20over%20many%20of%20its%20critical%20wetlands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20built%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F01%2F08%2Farts%2Fdesign%2Ftaking-parking-lots-seriously-as-public-spaces.html%3Fmcubz%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efar%20too%20much%20parking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Residents%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edisenchanted%20with%20townhome%20density%20have%20created%20sprawling%20exurbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20massive%20success%20of%20Houston's%20minimum%20lot%20size%20reform%20is%20getting%20noticed%20across%20Texas%20and%20around%20the%20country.%20Last%20summer%2C%20the%20city%20council%20of%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20passed%20a%20measure%20to%20cut%20its%20minimum%20lot%20size%20for%20a%20single-family%20home%20from%205%2C750%20square%20feet%20to%202%2C500%20square%20feet.%20Auburn%2C%20Maine%2C%20and%20Helena%2C%20Montana%2C%20both%20got%20rid%20of%20minimum%20lot%20sizes%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20their%20cities%2C%20and%20a%20slew%20of%20state%20legislatures%2C%20including%20Arizona%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20and%20New%20York%2C%20are%20considering%20smaller%20lot%20requirements%2C%20Mercatus%20researcher%20Salim%20Furth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarketurbanism.com%2F2024%2F01%2F11%2Fresources-for-reformers-houstons-minimum-lot-sizes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHouston%20kind%20of%20has%20revealed%20a%20potential%20free%20lunch%20opportunity%20for%20cities%20that%20are%20struggling%20with%20getting%20more%20affordable%20homeownership%20opportunities%20built%2C%26quo