at-3.27.08-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ERony%20Cohen%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20remember%20any%20particular%20moment%20when%20she%20first%20became%20aware%20of%20the%20number%20tattooed%20on%20her%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20arm.%20It%20was%20just%20always%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20says%20she%20felt%20as%20if%20she%20had%20experienced%20the%20Holocaust%20herself%2C%20in%20a%20different%20cycle%20of%20her%20own%20life.%20It%20featured%20in%20her%20dreams.%20It%20permeated%20family%20life%2C%20as%20did%20the%20self-imposed%20interdiction%20on%20talking%20about%20the%20past%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20relatives.%20The%20legacy%20of%20starvation%20was%20never%20far%20from%20the%20surface.%20Food%20was%20used%20to%20soothe.%20There%20was%20no%20waste.%20Her%20grandfather%20finished%20every%20crumb%20from%20every%20plate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20the%20Holocaust%20has%20had%20through%20the%20generations%20runs%20deep.%20Quite%20how%20we%20remember%20the%20past%20and%20its%20legacy%20varies%20hugely.%20Cohen%20is%20one%20of%20a%20small%20but%20growing%20number%20of%20the%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%20who%20have%20replicated%20the%20Auschwitz%20death%20camp%20tattoo%20on%20their%20own%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Felie-wiesel-survived-auschwitz-to-give-us-a-vivid-glimpse-of-the-kingdom-of-night-62024%5C%22%3EAuschwitz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20Nazi-occupied%20Poland%2C%20was%20the%20only%20camp%20where%20numbers%20were%20tattooed%20on%20those%20inmates%20not%20selected%20for%20immediate%20death.%20In%20replacing%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%20this%20number%20has%20become%20the%20visual%20symbol%20of%20the%20crimes%20of%20the%20Nazis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20draws%20meaning%20from%20her%20tattoo%20in%20that%20it%20signifies%20her%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20her%20own%20identity%20as%20a%20descendant%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors.%20To%20her%20mind%2C%20replicating%20this%20number%20was%20a%20means%20of%20taking%20her%20grandmother%2C%20as%20a%20person%2C%20and%20her%20legacy%20forward.%20As%20a%20gesture%20and%20an%20indelible%20mark%20she%20carries%20with%20her%2C%20she%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20is%20my%20grandma.%20It%E2%80%99s%20my%20past%2C%20my%20roots%2C%20my%20story.%20It%E2%80%99s%20who%20I%20am.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20potent%20gesture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3EMy%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20delves%20into%20the%20stories%20of%20those%20descendants%20who%2C%20like%20Cohen%2C%20have%20chosen%20to%20replicate%20a%20parent%20or%20a%20grandparent%E2%80%99s%20tattoo%20on%20their%20own%20body.%20Of%20the%2016%20people%20I%20have%20spoken%20with%2C%2013%20are%20from%20Israel%20and%20three%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20number%20of%20remaining%20survivors%20of%20the%20Nazi%20concentration%20camps%20grows%20ever%20smaller%20and%20the%20Holocaust%20passes%20out%20of%20living%20memory%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3Ereplicating%20an%20Auschwitz%20tattoo%3C%2Fa%3E%20becomes%20an%20ever%20more%20potent%20gesture%20about%20embodied%20memorialisation%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20familial%20ties%20and%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20I%20have%20spoken%20with%20have%20relayed%20complex%20and%20varied%20decision-making%20processes%20behind%20this%20potent%20gesture.%20Some%20waited%20until%20their%20survivor%20parent%20or%20grandparent%20had%20died.%20Some%20got%20the%20tattoo%20without%20seeking%20approval.%20Others%20discussed%20doing%20so%20with%20their%20relative%2C%20beforehand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%2