ure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20replica%20tattoos%20they%20have%20each%20opted%20for%20vary%20in%20terms%20of%20font%2C%20colour%20and%20placement.%20Some%20have%20chosen%20to%20replicate%20exactly%20what%20the%20original%20looked%20like%20and%20where%20it%20was%20placed.%20Others%20have%20chosen%20to%20alter%20the%20designs%20in%20detail%20and%20colour%2C%20or%20to%20place%20it%20on%20a%20different%20part%20of%20their%20body.%20Each%20decision%20crafts%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20new%20tattoo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20I%20met%20with%20Orly%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20on%20Zoom.%20She%20had%20chosen%20to%20have%20her%20maternal%20grandfather%20Samuel%20Kestenbaum%E2%80%99s%20number%20tattooed%20on%20her%20arm%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20for%20her%20maternal%20grandmother%2C%20Agi%20Kestenbaum.%20She%20had%20been%20in%20Auschwitz%20too%2C%20but%20was%20not%20tattooed%20because%20she%20was%20not%20expected%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Cohen%2C%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20remember%20a%20specific%20time%20when%20she%20first%20noticed%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%2C%20but%20the%20stories%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20were%20a%20part%20of%20her%20life%20from%20childhood.%20She%20says%20her%20mother%2C%20who%20died%20eight%20years%20before%20we%20spoke%2C%20used%20to%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20Holocaust.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20knew%20everything%2C%E2%80%9D%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20four%20of%20her%20grandparents%20had%20survived%20the%20Holocaust.%20Her%20paternal%20grandparents%20died%20when%20she%20was%20in%20her%20late%20teens%20and%20even%20now%2C%20she%20says%2C%20her%20father%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20what%20they%20experienced.%20She%20says%20that%20when%20she%20asks%20her%20father%20questions%2C%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know%20the%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeintraub%20Gilad%20remains%20very%20close%20to%20her%20grandmother%2C%20who%20is%2095%20years%20old.%20The%20tattoo%20gives%20her%20the%20chance%20to%20continue%20what%20her%20mother%20used%20to%20do%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20Holocaust.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20starts%20the%20conversation%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%E2%80%99s%20the%20thing%20that%20my%20grandmother%20is%20so%20happy%20about.%20She%20knows%20that%20after%20she%E2%80%99s%20gone%2C%20that%20I%20will%20talk.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tattoo%20itself%20features%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%20in%20a%20nest%20of%20leafy%20green%20vines.%20From%20different%20vines%20emerge%20letters%2C%20the%20initials%20of%20the%20names%20of%20Weintraub%20Gilad%E2%80%99s%20husband%20and%20her%20children.%20But%20the%20resulting%20composition%20is%20as%20much%20about%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20history%20as%20it%20is%20about%20their%20collective%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20choice%20of%20green%20vines%20and%20leaves%20came%20from%20her%20love%20of%20nature.%20Her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%20was%20on%20his%20left%20arm%2C%20but%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20placed%20her%20own%20tattoo%20on%20her%20right%20arm.%20She%20says%20she%20wanted%20%E2%80%9Cto%20do%20it%20the%20same%20but%20different%E2%80%9D.%20One%20reason%20for%20choosing%20the%20right%20arm%20was%20because%20she%20did%20not%20want%20to%20see%20the%20number%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20side%20of%20the%20heart%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20summer%2C%20I%20spoke%20with%20Yair%20Ron%20(Reisz)%2C%20also%20on%20Zoom.%20He%20grew%20up%20in%20Israel%2C%20on%20a%20kibbutz%20founded%20by%20Holocaust%20survivors.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20very%20small%20community%20of%20people%20with%20same%20idea%20of%20communism%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20them%20were%20Holocaust%20survivors%2C%20so%20all%20of%20them%20have%20numbers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20no%20one%20on%20the%20kibbutz%20had%20grandparents%20or%20spoke%20about%20their%20suffering.%20Ron%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Jakub%20Reisz%20%E2%80%93%20whom%20everyone%20knew%20as%20Yakshi%20%E2%80%93%20said%20nothing%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20and%2C%20like%20many%20children%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%2C%20Ron%20and%20his%20sister%20knew%20not%20to%20ask.%20Yakshi%20would%20talk%20about%20helping%20people%20escape%20from%20Slovakia%20to%20Hungary%20%E2%80%93%20but%20he%20never%20said%20a%20word%20about%20what%20he%20had%20experienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20impossible%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20with%20my%20father.%20We%20were%20afraid%20to%20ask%20and%20afraid%20to%20hear.%20Maybe%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20hear.%20And%20he%20told%20us%20that%20he%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20tell%2C%20so%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20exchange%20any%20information%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20whatsoever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERon%20first%20noticed%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20number%20as%20a%20child.%20Just%20as%20it%20was%20normal%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20things%20%E2%80%93%20about%20families%2C%20generations%2C%20loss%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20also%20normal%20to%20him%20and%20his%20peers%20that%20adults%20had%20numbers%20on%20their%20bodies.%20Until%20he%20started%20venturing%20out%20into%20the%20local%20town%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20really%20meet%20people%20from%20outside%20of%20the%20kibbutz%20%E2%80%93%20adults%2C%20that%20is%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seemed%20very%20natural%20to%20us%20that%20adults%20had%20numbers%20so%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20pay%20very%20much%20attention%20to%20this.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20other%20adults%20or%20people%20without%20numbers.%20The%20kibbutz%20was%20far%20away%20in%20the%20mountain%2C%20it%20was%20very%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(m