chmann%20is%20sentenced%20to%20death%20in%20Jerusalem%20on%20December%2015%201961.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%201967%2C%20Israel%20responded%20to%20threats%20from%20Egypt%20and%20other%20neighbouring%20states%20with%20an%20offensive%20that%20allowed%20it%20to%20expand%20into%20and%20occupy%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%20Further%20afield%2C%20the%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20known%20as%20the%20six-day%20war%20%E2%80%93%20built%20an%20affinity%20between%20Jewish%20communities%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Israel.%20Many%20American%20Jews%20began%20to%20both%20embrace%20their%20European%20roots%20and%20support%20Zionism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWieviorka%E2%80%99s%20book%20highlights%20the%20third%20(and%20ongoing)%20phase%20of%20Holocaust%20memorialisation%20%E2%80%93%20what%20she%20terms%20the%20%E2%80%9Cera%20of%20the%20witness%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20emerged%20in%20the%201970s.%20People%20started%20collating%20survivor%20testimonies%2C%20photographs%20and%20documentation.%20Through%20visits%20to%20Poland%2C%20to%20the%20camps%20and%20ghettos%2C%20families%20began%20to%20tell%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnyupress.org%2F9781479839292%2Fthe-holocaust-across-generations%2F%5C%22%3Estories%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20visit%20to%20Poland%20triggered%20the%20idea%20of%20replicating%20the%20Auschwitz%20number%20on%20their%20own%20body.%20In%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20I%20spoke%20with%20Zeev%20Forkosh.%20Now%20aged%2038%2C%20he%20has%20multiple%20tattoos%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20idea%20for%20his%20first%20one%20came%20after%20going%20to%20Auschwitz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20information%20Forkosh%20learned%20during%20that%20trip%2C%20about%20what%20his%20grandmother%20had%20experienced%20there%2C%20sparked%20such%20powerful%20emotions%20that%20he%20decided%20to%20get%20a%20Holocaust%20memorial%20tattoo.%20He%20describes%20the%20large%20Star%20of%20David%20he%20wears%20on%20his%20back%20as%20entwined%20with%20%E2%80%9Cbones%2C%20flesh%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20clothes%2C%20like%20the%20Holocaust%20survivors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Forkosh%20decided%20to%20replicate%20his%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20number%20on%20his%20arm%2C%20explaining%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20never%20forget%20this%20trip%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20on%20my%20back%20now.%20But%20after%20a%20few%20years%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20specific%20about%20my%20grandmother.%20I%20told%20the%20tattoo%20artist%20that%20this%20was%20for%20%5Bher%5D.%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20third%20generation%20of%20a%20Holocaust%20survivor.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20most%20beautiful%20tattoo%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20of%20this%20number%20in%20terms%20of%20beauty%20underscores%20how%20reproducing%20the%20tattoo%20gives%20it%20new%20meaning.%20It%20is%20a%20gesture%20that%2C%20for%20Forkosh%2C%20turns%20the%20visual%20symbol%20of%20a%20genocide%20into%20a%20symbol%20of%20love%20and%20legacy%2C%20of%20commemoration%20and%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20an%20arm%20tattoo.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D302%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%