ent%26quot%3B%20the%20Pentagon%20would%20step%20in%20during%20a%20blockade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20threshold%20for%20US%20military%20intervention%20in%20Taiwan%20likely%20isn't%20an%20invasion%20from%20China%2C%20but%20a%20lesser%20action%20such%20as%20Beijing%20quarantining%20or%20blockading%20the%20island%2C%20according%20to%20a%20loose%20consensus%20from%20leading%20experts%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20based%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fsurveying-experts-us-and-taiwan-views-chinas-approach-taiwan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Washington-based%20foreign%20policy%20think-tank%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20%26amp%3B%20International%20Studies%2C%20or%20CSIS.%20The%20report%20was%20released%20on%20January%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20report%2C%20titled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fsurveying-experts-us-and-taiwan-views-chinas-approach-taiwan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSurveying%20the%20Experts%3A%20U.S.%20and%20Taiwan%20Views%20on%20China's%20Approach%20to%20Taiwan%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20center%20said%20it%20polled%2052%20US%20experts%2C%20including%20academics%2C%20people%20with%20extensive%20experience%20in%20the%20US%20government%2C%20and%20think-tank%20experts%20who%20have%20testified%20in%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2063%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20said%20they%20were%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bmoderately%20confident%26quot%3B%20the%20US%20military%20would%20step%20in%20should%20Beijing%20enact%20a%20quarantine%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20quarantine%20involves%20cordoning%20off%20Taiwan's%20flow%20of%20goods%20through%20non-military%20means%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20An%20example%20would%20be%20the%20use%20of%20a%20strict%20customs%20inspection%20regime%20that%20squeezes%20maritime%20traffic%20to%20the%20island's%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20naval%20blockade%2C%20in%20which%20China%20encircles%20the%20island%20with%20its%20forces%2C%20would%20also%20separately%20be%20likely%20to%20prompt%20the%20US%20military%20to%20act%2C%20said%2079%25%20of%20the%20experts%2C%20who%20indicated%20they%20were%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bmoderately%20confident%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20majority%20rises%20to%2088%25%20if%20the%20blockade%20includes%20Beijing%20launching%20strikes%20on%20Taiwan%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20of%20the%20surveyed%20experts%20%E2%80%94%2096%25%20%E2%80%94%20said%20the%20US%20would%20join%20the%20fight%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-doesnt-have-military-power-invade-taiwan-experts-csis-us-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20were%20to%20fully%20invade%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20quarantine%20or%20blockade%20could%20notably%20be%20the%20precursor%20to%20a%20full%20amphibious%20invasion%20by%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%2C%20CSIS'%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EExperts%20aren't%20confident%20that%20US%20allies%20will%20get%20involved%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20experts%20weren't%20as%20confident%20that%20US%20allies%20would%20jump%20into%20the%20conflict.%20Only%2029%25%20said%20a%20quarantine%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20US-led%20multinational%20effort%20to%20defend%20Taiwan%2C%20while%2033%25%20said%20a%20blockade%20with%20no%20strikes%20would%20create%20a%20coalition%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2060%25%20of%20the%20experts%20were%20confident%20that%20US%20allies%20would%20assist%20militarily%20if%20China%20were%20to%20invade%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECSIS%20also%20surveyed%2035%20experts%20and%20scholars%20from%20Taiwan%2C%20who%20were%20less%20optimistic%20about%20US%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForty%20percent%20expressed%20confidence%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20would%20aid%20Taipei%20if%20China%20were%20to%20enact%20a%20quarantine%2C%20while%2060%25%20indicated%20the%20US%20military%20would%20help%20in%20response%20to%20a%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2072%25%20believe%20the%20US%20would%20step%20in%20if%20China%20invaded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20how%20long%20they%20thought%20Taiwan%20could%20hold%20China%20off%20without%20the%20US%20military%2C%2090%25%20of%20the%20US%20experts%20indicated%20%26quot%3B2%20weeks%20to%201%20month%26quot%3B%20or%20longer%2C%20while%2089%25%20of%20the%20Taiwanese%20experts%20indicated%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20percent%20on%20both%20sides%20believed%20a%20lone%20Taiwan%20could%20last%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20experts%20were%20polled%20from%20November%20to%20December%202023%2C%20CSIS%20said%2C%20a%20time%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-xi-meeting-china-plan-supplant-us-working-apec-summit-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS-China%20relations%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20fraught%20with%20tension%20and%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-xi-pull-away-from-brink-conflict-apec-meeting-china-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20met%20personally%20with%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20San%20Francisco%20for%20the%20APEC%202023%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20leaders%20highlighted%20areas%20of%20cooperation%20in%20a%20rare%20positive%20sign%20for%20international%20ties%2C%20but%20the%20strain%20continues%20to%20build%20as%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%94%20a%20major%20flashpoint%20for%20a%20US-China%20war%20%E2%80%94%20elected%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaiwan-election-president-william-lai-ching-te-xi-china-hates-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWilliam%20Lai%20Ching-te%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Progressive%20party%20as%20its%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELai's%20party%2C%20under%20the%20outgoing%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%2C%20has%20long%20been%20opposed%20to%20Beijing's%20attempts%20to%20pressure%20