support%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20months%2C%20rumours%20that%20Nitish%20may%20join%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20again%20had%20been%20rife%20but%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20silence%20over%20the%20matter%2C%20even%20as%20he%20publicly%20expressed%20his%20anguish%20over%20lack%20of%20any%20progress%20in%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20at%20least%20twice%2C%20left%20the%20political%20pot%20boiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20submitting%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20governor%2C%20Rajendra%20Arlekar%2C%20on%20Sunday%20morning%20that%20Nitish%20confirmed%20all%20rumours%2C%20giving%20little%20chance%20to%20his%20former%20allies%20in%20INDIA%20to%20negotiate%2C%20cajole%20or%20convince%20him%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20opposition%20alliance.%20This%20lent%20further%20credence%20to%20the%20impression%20that%20Nitish%20had%20already%20decided%20to%20part%20ways%20with%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20resigned%20as%20CM%20today%20and%20have%20asked%20the%20Governor%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20this%20government.%20Party%20leaders%20were%20giving%20me%20advice.%20I%20heard%20what%20they%20said%20and%20have%20resigned.%20The%20situation%20was%20not%20good.%20So%2C%20we%20have%20broken%20ties%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitish%20said%20in%20his%20usual%20taciturn%20style%20while%20announcing%20his%20decision%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20working%20on%20an%20alliance%20(INDIA)%20for%20the%20last%201.5%20years%20but%20things%20were%20not%20working%20out.%20Now%2C%20we%20will%20form%20a%20new%20alliance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20the%20past%2C%20when%20he%20similarly%20switched%20camps%2C%20he%20evaded%20appearing%20in%20the%20public%20to%20clarify%20doubts%2C%20remained%20unreachable%20to%20his%20allies%20who%20attempted%20to%20contact%20him%20multiple%20times%2C%20and%20focused%20solely%20on%20mapping%20out%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20deal%20with%20the%20saffron%20party%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChasing%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20political%20ambitions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Nitish%20secured%20his%20first%20full-term%20tenure%20as%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%202005%2C%20he%20has%20barely%20been%20in%20an%20oppositional%20space.%20Barring%20a%20few%20months%20here%20and%20there%2C%20every%20decision%20that%20the%20septuagenarian%20leader%20took%20reasserted%20his%20own%20indispensability%20in%20Bihar%2C%20even%20when%20making%20new%20alliances.%20He%20has%20survived%2C%20and%20survived%20beyond%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20imagination%2C%20while%20remaining%20in%20power%20or%20pulling%20the%20strings%20of%20power%20ceaselessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20Nitish%20had%20his%20own%20political%20ambitions%20in%20mind%20every%20time%20he%20switched%20camps.%20He%20remained%20with%20the%20BJP%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20primary%20rival%20RJD%20in%20Bihar%20for%20years%2C%20but%20ended%20this%20alliance%20as%20he%20could%20foresee%20the%20fate%20of%20allies%20with%20the%20seemingly%20totalitarian%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ascent%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Nitish%20recharged%20his%20own%20position%20by%20quitting%20the%20NDA%20and%20beating%20the%20BJP%20with%20the%20help%20of%20its%20arch%20rival%20RJD%20in%20the%202015%20state%20assembly%20polls.%20Having%20delivered%20a%20striking%20message%20to%20Modi%20about%20his%20political%20significance%2C%20he%20went%20back%20to%20the%20NDA%20where%20he%20had%20been%20the%20most%20comfortable%20in%20his%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20relationship%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20however%2C%20took%20the%20biggest%20hit%20when%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%20allegedly%20engineered%20substantial%20losses%20for%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Lok%20Janshakti%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Chirag%20Paswan%20in%20the%202020%20assembly%20polls.%20BJP%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20state%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20ended%20up%20with%20its%20best%20tally%20(74)%2C%20while%20Janata%20Dal%20finished%20with%20one%20of%20its%20worst%20performances%20as%20a%20NDA%20constituent%20with%20merely%2043%20seats.%20Things%20took%20a%20final%20hit%20when%20he%20lost%20his%20closest%20aide%20R.C.P.%20Singh%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Singh%20was%20swiftly%20made%20a%20Union%20minister%2C%20even%20as%20the%20BJP%20attempted%20to%20poach%20JD(U)%E2%80%99s%20legislators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20only%20prominent%20BJP%20ally%20in%20India%20as%20others%20like%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(Badal)%20or%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20had%20already%20left%20the%20NDA%20because%20of%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20disregard%20for%20alliance%20politics.%20Yet%2C%20Nitish%20survived%20by%20quickly%20joining%20ranks%20with%20the%20RJD%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20national%20goal%20to%20help%20create%20a%20larger%20opposition%20front%20against%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20is%20now%20back%20in%20the%20NDA%2C%20masterfully%20securing%20his%20position%20as%20the%20most%20valuable%20ally%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Bihar%20yet%20again.%20The%20saffron%20party%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20missed%20a%20window%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20Nitish%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Its%20senior%20leaders%20hit%20out%20at%20Nitish%20on%20almost%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20with%20even%20the%20prime%20minister%20lashing%20out%20at%20him%20quite%20a%20few%20times%20in%20his%20speeches.%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20compared%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejungle%20raaj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20BJP%20leaders%20built%20a%20campaign%20around%20alleged%20corruption%2C%20misgovernance%2C%20and%20failing%20law%20and%20order%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20Nitish%20operated%20through%20this%20mesh%20of%20political%20dynamics%20is%20known%2C%20but%20by%20accepting%20him%20again%2C%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP%20has%20shown%20that%20it%20prioritises%20its%20electoral%20ambitions%20much%20more%20than%20its%20rhetoric%20of%20good%20governance%20and%20political%20ethics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20big%20blow%20for%20INDIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%20Over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20he%20had%20handed%20over%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20reins%20to%20his%20deputy%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%2C%20while%20touring%20the%20country%20to%20bring%20together%20a%20range%20of%20regional%20and%20national%20parties%20under%20a%20common%20umbrella.%20Most%20of%20these%20parties%20have%20been%20historically%20inimical%20to%20the%20Congress.%20Bringing%20them%20all%20together%20to%20ally%20with%20the%20Congress%20required%20negotiations%20that%20only%20a%20senior%20leader%20with%20political%20acumen%20like%20Nitish%20could%20have%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20he%20was%20instrumental%20in%20conducting%20a%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar%2C%20which%20gave%20a%20fillip%20to%20the%20opposition%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20Congress.%20The%20demand%20for%20a%20pan-India%20caste%20census%20re-energised%20Mandal%20politics%20and%20put%20the%20BJP%20on%20the%20backfoot%2C%20even%20if%20temporarily.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Nitish%20government%20foregrounded%20issues%20like%20employment%20and%20welfare%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%20by%20appointing%20over%20three%20lakh%20youth%20in%20state%20government%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20success%20of%20INDIA%20as%20a%20front%2C%20that%20also%20fended%20off%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20third%20front%20in%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20displayed%20his%20frustration%20with%20its%20lack%20of%20progress.%20His%20first%20dissent%20came%20in%20November%202023%20when%20he%20showed%20his%20anguish%20over%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffor-india-to-work-the-congress-must-take-a-step-back%5C%22%3Elethargic%20approach%20towards%20the%20opposition%20front%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20grand-old%20party%E2%80%99s%20sole%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20assembly%20polls%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20lost%20all%20the%20three%20Hindi-heartland%20states%2C%20despite%20showing%20great%20confidence%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20polls.%20However%2C%20if%20someone%20needs%20to%20take%20the%20blame%20in%20triggering%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20they%20will%20have%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20ministers%20of%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Delhi%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20The%20two%20leaders%20mooted%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20INDIA%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20in%20the%20long-delayed%20INDIA%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20December%2019%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20called%20by%20the%20Congress%20was%20supposed%20to%20happen%20on%20December%206%2C%202023%20but%20leaders%20like%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%20expressed%20their%20unavailability%2C%20indicating%20their%20discomfort%20with%20the%20alliance.%20Then%2C%20when%20the%20meeting%20happened%20eventually%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20surprisingly%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20Kharge%20as%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20without%20discussing%20it%20with%20any%20of%20the%20other%20leaders.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Congress%20was%20recovering%20from%20its%20losses%20in%20assembly%20elections%20and%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20explaining%20to%20do%20in%20front%20of%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20discussions%20on%20prime%20ministerial%20candidates%20appeared%20to%20be%20premature%2C%20when%20basics%20like%20seat-sharing%2C%20campaign%20strategy%20and%20joint%20action%20programmes%20had%20not%20been%20finalised.%20The%20fact%20that%20TMC%20spokespersons%20went%20on%20record%20after%20the%20fourth%20INDIA%20meeting%20on%20December%2019%20to%20suggest%20that%20INDIA%20will%20finalise%20seat-sharing%20by%20December%2031%20also%20looked%20improbable%2C%20forcing%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20general%20secretary%20(organisation)%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20and%20RJD%20chief%20Lalu%20Prasad%20to%20refute%20the%20TMC%20in%20their%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20recall%20how%20Nitish%20had%20braved%20media%20questions%20on%20a%20probable%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20when%20he%20was%20meeting%20leaders%20to%20formalise%20the%20alliance.%20Having%20known%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20preference%20to%20reduce%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9CModi%20vs%20%E2%80%98who%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20presidential%20style%2C%20Nitish%20had%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccollective%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20in%20INDIA%20and%20persistently%20maintained%20that%20the%20alliance%20will%20fight%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20by%20highlighting%20the%20concerns%20of%20common%20people%20and%20canvassing%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20authoritarian%20and%20centralising%20impulses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mischievous%20moves%20by%20Banerjee%20and%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20have%20now%20made%20their%20minds%20clear%20by%20announcing%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20alliance%20with%20the%20Congress%20in%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Punjab%2C%20undermined%20Nitish%20and%20other%20regional%20leaders%20of%20INDIA%2C%20and%20created%20a%20political%20narrative%20that%20was%20vastly%20different%20from%20what%20INDIA%20leaders%20had%20originally%20intended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20how%20Nitish%20had%20already%20expressed%20his%20view%20about%20the%20supposed%20%E2%80%9Clack%20of%20seriousness%E2%80%9D%20in%20India%2C%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20hasty%20decision%20to%20train%20its%20energy%20on%20the%20second%20round%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20even%20before%20the%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20strategy%20was%20chalked%20out%2C%20may%20have%20come%20as%20a%20final%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20has%20not%20bothered%20with%20monikers%20like%20%E2%80%9Cchameleon%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ekursi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chair)%20Kumar%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20%E2%80%9Cpaltu%20ram%E2%80%9D%20thrown%20at%20him%20ever%20in%20his%20political%20career.%20He%20has%20never%20owned%20ideological%20ethics.%20He%20has%20rather%20taken%20pride%20in%20his%20pragmatism%20and%20effectiveness.%20With%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20formidable%20opposition%20alliance%20in%20Bihar%20and%20its%2040%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20has%20broken.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20too%2C%20will%20sorely%20miss%20his%20strategic%20thinking%20and%20political%20acumen%20in%20taking%20on%20the%20dominant%20BJP.%20Nitish%20could%20have%20been%20an%20asset%20for%20the%20alliance%2C%20given%20his%20deep%20political%20experience%20in%20the%20Hindi%20heartland.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706439998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28163221%2F400924413_926965212122173_7713585483950685171_n.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nitish%E2%80%99s%20exit%20will%20come%20as%20a%20cruel%20blow%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%20In%20more%20ways%20than%20one%2C%20Nitish%20was%20the%20chief%20architect%20of%20INDIA.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnitish-kumar-india-alliance-exit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20the%20ICJ%20to%20Say%20It%20Is%20'Plausible'%20That%20Israel%20Is%20Carrying%20Out%20Genocide%20Is%20a%20Defining%20Moment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28140819%2FGEw1UHwXMAEPdVM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20charging%20Israel%20with%20genocide%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ficj-says-israel-must-comply-with-genocide-convention-but-stops-short-of-halting-military-operation%5C%22%3Eprovisional%20measures%20were%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2026%2C%20is%20a%20marker%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20conflict%20raging%20currently%2C%20and%20posits%20a%20moral%20prism%20to%20view%20the%20competing%20narratives.%20Raphael%20Lemkin%2C%20a%20legal%20scholar%20and%20a%20World%20War%20II%20refugee%20from%20Western%20Ukraine%20who%20lost%20considerable%20family%20in%20the%20Shoah%2C%20is%20widely%20considered%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20which%20was%20a%20direct%20reaction%20to%20the%20Holocaust.%20Legal%20defences%20aside%2C%20that%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20state%20sanctioned%20largely%20by%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20shame%20over%20allowing%20the%20Nazi%20Holocaust%20to%20occur%2C%20today%20faces%20a%20credible%20charge%20of%20genocide%20is%20a%20tragic%20irony%20of%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELemkin%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20war%20studying%20Nazi%20documents%20and%20ordinances%20to%20analyse%20the%20motive%20underlying%20Nazi%20repression%20and%20massacres%2C%20which%20today%20we%20understand%20to%20be%20archetypically%20genocidal%2C%20including%20implementing%20%3Cem%3ELebensraum%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20colonial%20stratagem%20previously%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fsurviving-genocide-colonial-namibia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployed%20by%20the%20Germans%20in%20Namibia%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20used%20to%20depopulate%20territories%20for%20settling%20Germans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20the%20seemingly%20indiscriminate%20killings%20of%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20by%20Israeli%20bombardment%2C%20which%20may%20be%20a%20war%20crime%20in%20itself%2C%20but%20the%20motive%20behind%20it%20which%20is%20called%20into%20question%20in%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case.%20Lemkin%20in%20his%20writing%20explained%20that%20genocide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.preventgenocide.org%2Flemkin%2Ffreeworld1945.htm%5C%22%3Erefers%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20plan%20%E2%80%9Caimed%20at%20destruction%20of%20the%20essential%20foundations%20of%20the%20life%20of%20national%20groups%20so%20that%20these%20groups%20wither%20and%20die%20like%20plants%20that%20have%20suffered%20a%20blight%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FLemkinInstitute%2Fstatus%2F1714599755609718970%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELemkin%20Institute%20for%20Genocide%20Prevention%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20now%20deleted%20post%20by%20the%20%40IsraelPM%20X%20handle%20%E2%80%9Cis%20an%20expression%20of%20genodical%20intent%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20which%20it%20was%20written%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhis%20is%20a%20struggle%20between%20the%20children%20of%20the%20light%20and%20the%20children%20of%20darkness%2C%20between%20humanity%20and%20the%20law%20of%20the%20jungle%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20lots%20of%20other%20statements%20too%20and%20the%20question%20sought%20to%20be%20answered%20in%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20case%20is%20whether%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20Israeli%20military%20campaign%20itself%2C%20and%2For%20the%20public%20declarations%20of%20collective%20punishment%2C%20and%2For%20the%20cutting%20off%20of%20water%2C%20food%20and%20fuel%20supplies%2C%20were%20sufficient%20for%20the%20court%20to%20prescribe%20emergency%20interim%20measures%20that%20Israel%20must%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20attacks%20on%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20often%20by%20or%20in%20aid%20of%20Israeli%20settlers%2C%20also%20raises%20concerns%20on%20genocidal%20intent.%20For%20its%20parts%2C%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20in%20the%20ICJ%20did%20not%20link%20the%20settlement%20policies%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20ICJ%20is%20considering%20a%20separate%20advisory%20opinion%20on%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fcase-related%2F186%2F186-20231114-pre-01-00-en.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20policies%20and%20practices%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territories%2C%20including%20East%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fhome%5C%22%3Epreliminary%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%2026%2C%20the%20ICJ%20found%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cplausible%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20sufficiently%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20it%20to%20direct%20provisional%20measures.%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20which%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20has%20said%20was%20set%20up%20to%20ensure%20that%20a%20Holocaust%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20again%E2%80%9D%20happens%20%E2%80%93%20is%20prime%20facie%20indicated%20to%20be%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%20The%20ICJ%20took%20note%20of%20the%20conduct%20of%20Israeli%20forces%2C%20statements%20of%20UN%20officials%20and%20Israeli%20officials%2C%20and%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20in%20itself.%20It%20also%20took%20note%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20Committee%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20Racial%20Discrimination%20which%20found%20%E2%80%9Cracist%20hate%20speech%E2%80%9D%20and%20an%20expert%20group%E2%80%99s%20report%20that%20found%20%E2%80%9Cdiscernibly%20genocidal%20and%20dehumanising%20rhetoric%E2%80%9D.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20self-declared%20steps%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20were%20held%20to%20be%20insufficient%20to%20remove%20the%20risk%20of%20%E2%80%9Cirreparable%20prejudice%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20under%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22By%20Invoking%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20ICJ%20Makes%20It%20Clear%20Israel's%20Killing%20of%20Palestinians%20is%20Not%20'War'%20But%20Crime%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fby-invoking-genocide-convention-icj-makes-it-clear-israels-killing-of-palestinians-is-not-war-but-crime%5C%22%3EBy%20Invoking%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20ICJ%20Makes%20It%20Clear%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Killing%20of%20Palestinians%20is%20Not%20%E2%80%98War%E2%80%99%20But%20Crime%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fnode%2F203452%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseparate%20opinion%20as%20judge%20ad%20joc%20appointed%20by%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%2C%20as%20he%20emphatically%20notes%2C%20its%20agent%20%E2%80%93%20Aharon%20Barak%2C%20a%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Israeli%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20has%20anguish%20seeping%20through%20his%20words.%20He%20evokes%20the%20memory%20of%20Lemkin.%20Barak%20was%20a%20five%20year%20old%20when%20Nazis%20put%20him%20with%20his%20family%20in%20a%20ghetto%2C%20and%20he%20is%20himself%20a%20survivor%20of%20the%20genocide%20in%20Lithuania.%20He%20writes%20that%20%E2%80%9C%5Bg%5Denocide%20is%20more%20than%20a%20word%20for%20me%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cidea%20that%20Israel%20is%20now%20accused%20of%20committing%20genocide%20is%20very%20hard%20for%20me%20personally%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20His%20statement%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevery%20Israeli%20soldier%20carries%20with%20him%20(or%20her)%20in%20their%20backpack%2C%20the%20rules%20of%20international%20law%E2%80%9D%20will%20jar%20those%20watching%20the%20bombardment%20live.%20However%2C%20even%20though%20Barak%20finds%20no%20plausible%20links%20to%20genocidal%20intent%2C%20he%20struggles%20with%20the%20situation%20and%20votes%20for%20humanitarian%20aid%20and%20the%20direction%20to%20stop%20incitement%20to%20genocide%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdecrease%20tensions%20and%20discourage%20damaging%20rhetoric%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20make%20or%20break%20moment%20in%20international%20law.%20Although%20no%20state%20has%20formally%20joined%20the%20case%20with%20South%20Africa%2C%20the%20divide%20in%20those%20indicating%20support%20and%20those%20against%20runs%20through%20a%20global%20north-south%20divide.%20Of%20the%20BRICS%20countries%2C%20Brazil%20has%20supported%20South%20Africa%20explicitly%2C%20and%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20been%20sympathetic.%20India%20has%20been%20silent%20on%20the%20case.%20The%20global%20north%20has%20come%20out%20against%20the%20case%20itself%2C%20and%20as%20traditional%20exponents%20of%20what%20they%20call%20the%20international%20%E2%80%98rules-based%20order%E2%80%99%2C%20countries%20such%20as%20Germany%2C%20which%20has%20referred%20to%20the%20historical%20necessity%20to%20support%20Israel%2C%20are%20faced%20with%20difficult%20choices.%20Canada%20has%20been%20another%20vocal%20supporter%20of%20Israeli%20actions%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20its%20oft%20stated%20position%20as%20a%20stronger%20supporter%20of%20international%20law.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeas.europa.eu%2Feeas%2Ficj-joint-statement-high-representative-and-european-commission_en%5C%22%3EEU%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20quick%20to%20announce%20after%20the%20order%20that%20ICJ%20judgments%20are%20binding%20and%20it%20expects%20compliance.%20This%20can%20only%20lead%20to%20a%20churn%20in%20the%20international%20system%2C%20and%20a%20shift%20towards%20more%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politik%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20a%20passing%20of%20some%20of%20the%20power%20enjoyed%20by%20traditional%20exponents.%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20bringing%20the%20case%20is%20in%20itself%20indicative%20of%20that%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20bringing%20the%20case%2C%20South%20Africa%20is%20not%20just%20exercising%20its%20legal%20right%20as%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20but%20also%20discharging%20an%20obligation%20flowing%20from%20the%20moral%20authority%20of%20Nelson%20Mandela%2C%20who%20was%20an%20ardent%20supporter%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%2C%20and%20considered%20himself%20in%20solidarity%20with%2C%20and%20in%20debt%20to%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20leadership%20for%20its%20support%20of%20the%20African%20National%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20against%20apartheid.%20Consistent%20with%20this%20history%20was%20Israel%20and%20Apartheid%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Ereal%20politik%20%3C%2Fem%3Emutual%20support.%20There%20are%20also%20suggestions%20that%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20due%20to%20the%20need%20to%20shore%20up%20domestic%20support%20for%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%2C%20but%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20motives%20are%20strictly%20cynical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20bring%20a%20case%20was%20a%20particularly%20Lemkinesque%20insertion%20into%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%2C%20which%20made%20the%20crime%20of%20genocide%20a%20crime%20against%20all%20humanity%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Ehostis%20generis%20humani%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20thereby%20making%20it%C2%A0the%20duty%20of%20every%20country%20to%20prevent%20such%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Explains%20the%20Desensitisation%20of%20the%20Western%20Leadership%20Towards%20Horrors%20in%20Gaza%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-explains-the-desensitisation-of-the-western-leadership-towards-horrors-in-gaza%5C%22%3EWhat%20Explains%20the%20Desensitisation%20of%20the%20Western%20Leadership%20Towards%20Horrors%20in%20Gaza%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20not%20carry%20out%20genocide%2C%20to%20disallow%20and%20prosecute%20the%20public%20and%20direct%20incitement%20to%20genocide%2C%20to%20allow%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20and%20to%20report%20to%20the%20court%20with%20a%20copy%20to%20South%20Africa%20within%2030%20days.%20The%20court%20has%20no%20sheriff%20it%20can%20send%20to%20coerce%20compliance%2C%20but%20is%20a%20moral%20expression%20of%20international%20law%3B%20Israel%20and%20its%20supporters%20will%20find%20their%20arguments%20harder%20to%20make%20now%20that%20the%20ICJ%20has%20said%20there%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecase%20of%20genocide%20they%20are%20answerable%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20State%20now%20faces%20a%20choice%20%E2%80%93%20probably%20being%20articulated%20by%20many%20of%20its%20supporters%20%E2%80%93%20of%20hunkering%20down%20into%20an%20us-versus-the-rest-of-the-world%20mindset%2C%20and%20accusing%20the%20court%20of%20being%20a%20backer%20of%20terror%2C%20or%20of%20travelling%2C%20or%20be%20forced%20to%20travel%2C%20down%20the%20hard%20path%20to%20a%20re-think.%20The%20early%20signs%20are%20not%20encouraging.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAvi%20Singh%20is%20an%20advocate%20who%20specialises%20in%20transnational%20and%20international%20law%20and%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20International%20University%20College%2C%20Turin.%20He%20has%20also%20practiced%20before%20international%20criminal%20tribunals.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706439207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F28140819%2FGEw1UHwXMAEPdVM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffor-the-icj-to-say-it-is-plausible-that-israel-is-carrying-out-genocide-is-a-defining-moment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22That%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%2C%20a%20state%20sanctioned%20largely%20by%20the%20world's%20shame%20over%20allowing%20the%20Nazi%20Holocaust%20to%20occur%2C%20today%20faces%20a%20credible%20charge%20of%20genocide%20is%20a%20tragic%20irony%20of%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ffor-the-icj-to-say-it-is-plausible-that-israel-is-carrying-out-genocide-is-a-defining-moment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Holocaust%20survivor%20fears%20horrific%20event%20can%20happen%20again%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706436900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-lily-ebert-auschwitz_6435802.png%3F20240128112125%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fholocaust-survivor-fears-horrific-event-can-happen-again-13058459%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lily%20Ebert%2C%20one%20of%20the%20last%20remaining%20survivors%20from%20Auschwitz-Birkenau%2C%20told%20Sky%20News%20that%20she%20believes%20the%20Holocaust%20could%20happen%20again.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A309%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fholocaust-survivor-fears-horrific-event-can-happen-again-13058459%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fholocaust-survivor-fears-horrific-event-can-happen-again-13058459%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fholocaust-survivor-fears-horrific-event-can-happen-again-13058459%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Protesters%20throw%20soup%20at%20Mona%20Lisa%20painting%20in%20Paris%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706436720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-mona-lisa_6435837.jpg%3F20240128101747%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fprotesters-throw-soup-at-mona-lisa-painting-in-paris-13058454%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Protesters%20have%20thrown%20red%20soup%20at%20the%20Mona%20Lisa%20painting%20in%20the%20Louvre%20in%20Paris.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A404%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fprotesters-throw-soup-at-mona-lisa-painting-in-paris-13058454%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fprotesters-throw-soup-at-mona-lisa-painting-in-paris-13058454%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fprotesters-throw-soup-at-mona-lisa-painting-in-paris-13058454%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Draft%20UGC%20Guidelines%20Suggest%20De-Reserving%20Faculty%20Positions%20in%20Universities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29095001%2FScreenshot-2023-11-29-at-9.49.41-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%20has%20come%20up%20with%20draft%20rules%20to%20de-reserve%20the%20posts%20of%20faculty%20members%20in%20higher%20education%20institutions%20if%20%E2%80%98enough%20reserved%20candidates%20are%20not%20available%E2%80%99%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fthesundaystandard%2F2024%2FJan%2F28%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-seek-to-open-de-reservation-window%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20guidelines%20were%20released%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20December.%20They%20are%20open%20for%20public%20opinion%20till%20today.%20The%20posts%20in%20question%20are%20meant%20for%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20OBC%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20these%20posts%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20de-reserved%20for%20unreserved%20category%20candidates.%20But%20for%20Group%20A%20posts%2C%20a%20university%20can%20prepare%20a%20proposal%20for%20de-reservation%20as%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20allowed%20to%20remain%20vacant%20in%20%E2%80%98public%20interest%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20newspaper%20quoted%20the%20draft%20guidelines%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20do%20so%2C%20it%20would%20have%20to%20provide%20information%20like%20the%20designation%2C%20pay%20scale%2C%20name%20of%20the%20service%2C%20responsibilities%2C%20required%20qualifications%2C%20efforts%20made%20to%20fill%20the%20post%2C%20and%20why%20it%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20remain%20vacant%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Group%20C%20and%20D%20posts%20can%20be%20de-reserved%20by%20the%20executive%20council%20of%20the%20university%20itself%20while%20for%20Group%20A%20posts%2C%20the%20proposal%20has%20to%20be%20submitted%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20would%20apply%20to%20all%20the%20central%20universities%2C%20deemed-to-be-universities%2C%20and%20other%20autonomous%20bodies%2Finstitutions%20under%20the%20central%20government%20or%20those%20receiving%20grant-in-aid%20from%20the%20UGC%2C%20central%20government%2C%20or%20consolidated%20fund%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20rules%20would%20apply%20in%20promotion%20policies%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20rules%20argued%20that%20there%20has%20been%20a%20shortfall%20in%20reserved%20category%20posts%20and%20the%20institutions%20should%20fill%20the%20vacant%20posts%20by%20starting%20a%20recruitment%20drive%20for%20the%20second%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706435942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29095001%2FScreenshot-2023-11-29-at-9.49.41-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-suggest-de-reserving-faculty-positions-in-universities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20rules%20would%20apply%20in%20promotion%20policies%2C%20too.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdraft-ugc-guidelines-suggest-de-reserving-faculty-positions-in-universities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%221%2C480%20Square%20Yards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09172250%2FBabri-Masjid.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20disputed%20site%20on%20which%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20was%201%2C480%20square%20yards%20in%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20amount%20to%20less%20than%20many%20houses%20in%20Delhi%20and%20elsewhere.%20Clearly%2C%20no%20%3Cem%3Emandir%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20any%20consequence%20could%20have%20been%20built%20there.%20True%2C%20the%20legal%20dispute%20sprawled%20to%20the%202.77%20acres%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20state%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flddashboard.legislative.gov.in%2Factsofparliamentfromtheyear%2Facquisition-certain-area-ayodhya-act-1993%5C%22%3EAcquisition%20of%20Certain%20Area%20at%C2%A0Ayodhya%20Act%2C%201993%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20actual%20size%20was%20just%201%2C480%20square%20yards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20might%20legitimately%20argue%20what%20the%20controversy%20was%20about.%20The%20temple%20necessarily%20had%20to%20be%20built%20on%20the%20surrounding%20land%20already%20owned%20by%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20now%20sprawls%20over%20a%20huge%20area%2C%20not%20in%20dispute.%20Nor%20can%20it%20be%20said%20that%20the%20inner%20sanctum%20representing%20Lord%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20birth%20was%20placed%20exactly%20where%20the%20masjid%20was%20%E2%80%93%20as%20vehemently%20argued%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%E2%80%99s%20report%20to%20the%20court%20stated%20that%20it%20could%20not%20be%20conclusively%20said%20that%20Babur%20destroyed%20the%20temple%20to%20build%20a%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20the%20contestation%20dates%20back%20to%201857-8.%20It%20was%20futile%20to%20examine%20whether%20Muslims%20had%20possession%20before%201857.%20We%20must%20presume%20that%20they%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindu%20counter%20trespass%20in%201857-8%20found%20an%20encroachment%20to%20parts%20of%20the%20site.%20In%201885%2C%20the%20Commissioner%E2%80%99s%20Court%20authoritatively%20held%20that%20the%20Muslims%20had%20title%2C%20and%20the%20Hindus%20had%2C%20at%20best%2C%20a%20prescriptive%20right%20to%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20latter%20period%2C%20Muslims%20had%20access%20to%20the%20masjid%20even%20though%20attempts%20were%20made%20in%201935-6%20to%20damage%20the%20mosque.%20The%20Hindus%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20repair%20which%20was%20made%20by%20Muslims.%20This%20attempt%20to%20take%20the%20masjid%20by%20force%20and%20injure%20it%20was%20nothing%20new%20and%20culminated%20in%20its%20destruction%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-rss-bjp-vhp-ram-temple%5C%22%3EFour%20Decades%20of%20Milking%20a%20Deity%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Hindus%20continued%20to%20pray%20to%20the%20idol%20which%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20the%20Hindus%20%E2%80%93%20miraculously%20appeared%20in%20December%201949%2C%20it%20was%20due%20to%20court%20orders%20and%20could%20not%20give%20them%20title%20which%20was%20equally%20miraculously%20given%20to%20them%20in%20November%202019%20by%20the%20final%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20If%20the%20judgment%20is%20taken%20at%20face%20value%2C%20the%20masjid%20was%20destroyed%20in%201992%20on%20Hindu%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202019%20was%20shaky.%20Suit%20no.%205%20was%C2%A0filed%20in%201989%20and%20clearly%20outside%20limitation%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20we%20take%20December%201961%2C%20when%20the%20Sunni%20Board%20filed%20its%20case%20claiming%20title%2C%20as%20the%20start%20of%20the%20dispute.%20The%20limitation%20period%20is%2012%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Hindu%20suit%20of%201989%20was%20well%20within%20limitation.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20justification%20was%20that%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20deity%20not%20being%20party%20in%20the%20earlier%20suits%2C%20its%20interests%20were%20not%20being%20adequately%20protected%20in%20the%20earlier%20suits%20including%20those%20initiated%20by%20the%20Hindu%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Mahant%E2%80%99s%20case%20of%201959%20was%20to%20defend%20the%20Hindu%20cause%2C%20and%20did%20not%20claim%20title%20and%20was%20declared%20outside%20limitation.%20In%20a%20terse%20summation%20on%20the%201989%20suit%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20declared%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Creasons%20which%20weighed%20with%20Agarwal%20J.%20(in%20the%20High%20Court)%2C%20as%20summarised%20above%2C%20commend%20themselves%20for%20acceptance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENever%20was%20the%20question%20of%20limitation%20so%20sparsely%20disposed%20of.%20Nor%20can%20it%20be%20said%20that%20the%20title%20and%20possession%20were%20not%20with%20the%20Muslims%20at%20the%20time%20of%20trespass%20in%20December%201949%2C%20as%20advocate%20Zafaryab%20Jilani%20convincingly%20demonstrated%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20was%20an%20expensive%20farce.%20The%20farce%20was%20exacerbated%20recently%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20not%20applying%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPlaceWorshipAct1991.pdf%5C%22%3EPlaces%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provision)%20Act%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20present%20case%20involving%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20in%20Varanasi.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FJUD_2.pdf%5C%22%3EIn%20its%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20of%20November%209%2C%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20said%20the%201991%20Act%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20enforced%20a%20constitutional%20commitment%20and%20operationalised%20its%20constitutional%20obligations%20to%20uphold%20the%20equality%20of%20all%20religions%20and%20secularism%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20imposes%20a%20non-derogable%20obligation%20towards%20enforcing%20our%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20under%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20The%20law%20is%20hence%20a%20legislative%20instrument%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20secular%20features%20of%20the%20Indian%20polity%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Non-retrogression%20is%20a%20foundational%20feature%20of%20the%20fundamental%20constitutional%20principles%20of%20which%20secularism%20is%20a%20core%20component.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20is%20thus%20a%20legislative%20intervention%20which%20preserves%20non-retrogression%20as%20an%20essential%20feature%20of%20our%20secular%20values.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-places-of-worship-act-must-be-preserved%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Must%20Be%20Preserved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20was%20what%20the%201991%20Act%20said%20according%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20what%20happened%20to%20all%20this%20in%20its%20application%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%5C%22%3Econtroversies%20over%20Varanasi%20and%20now%20Mathura%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20many%20things%20in%20the%20Babri%20decisions%20were%20fudged%2C%20even%20though%20the%202019%20judgement%20was%20seen%20as%20liberation.%C2%A0We%20can%20re-write%20history%20but%20not%20ignore%20its%20fundamentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20appropriation%20of%20Lord%20Ram%20in%20Ayodhya%20is%20a%20thorn%20in%20the%20side%20of%20our%20governance.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20we%20do%20not%20follow%20the%20strict%20American%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20state%20from%20religion.%20But%20India%20does%20not%20reject%20that%20doctrine.%20If%20we%20follow%20the%20doctrine%20of%20principled%20equality%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20token%20visit%20to%20Muslim%20sites%20does%20not%20make%20the%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20to%20realise%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20Hindu%20state%20fuelled%20by%20Hindutva.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20wholly%20wrong%20when%20it%20ruled%20in%201995%20that%20Hindutva%20is%20not%20an%20appeal%20to%20religion%20in%20elections.%20This%20aggressive%20Hinduism%20is%20a%20step%20towards%20the%20Hinduisation%20of%20India%2C%20which%20is%20not%20an%20exercise%20in%20secularism%20but%20a%20political%20declaration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20complicit%20in%20this%20process%2C%20but%20it%20must%20otherwise%20also%20realise%20that%20it%20is%20unconstitutional%20to%20support%20a%20Hindu%20elected%20dictatorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Babri%20case%20and%20its%20inelegant%20aftermath%20have%20witnessed%20a%20crack%20in%20our%20polity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECelebrate%20Lord%20Ram%20by%20all%20means%2C%20but%20using%20the%20state%20to%20spend%20from%20its%20coffers%20in%20this%20celebration%20is%20far%20from%20appropriate%2C%20because%20it%20is%20dangerously%20divisive%2C%20as%20indeed%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Erath%20yatra%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20claim%20these%201%2C480%20square%20yards%20for%20which%20history%20was%20defiled%20and%20a%20tradition%20of%20healthy%20secularism%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20people%20develop%20this%20site%20not%20through%20politics.%20Will%20the%20same%20hype%20accompany%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fno-sign-of-new-ayodhya-mosque%5C%22%3Ethe%20masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20is%20built%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20the%20most%20diverse%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20more%20than%20many%20continents.%20It%20is%20this%20diversity%20that%20makes%20us%20unique.%20To%20abandon%20it%20destroys%20the%20India%20that%20is%20to%20be%20treasured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Frajeev-dhavan%2F%5C%22%3ERajeev%20Dhavan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20advocate%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20has%20represented%20Muslim%20parties%20in%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi-Babri%20Masjid%20title%20dispute%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706434983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09172250%2FBabri-Masjid.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F1480-square-yards%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22So%20many%20things%20in%20the%20Babri%20decisions%20were%20fudged%2C%20even%20though%20the%202019%20judgement%20was%20seen%20as%20liberation.%C2%A0We%20can%20re-write%20history%20but%20not%20ignore%20its%20fundamentals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F1480-square-yards%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Broadcast%20Bill%3A%20Intent%20to%20Over-Regulate%20Media%20Could%20Irreparably%20Damage%20Free%20Speech%2C%20Says%20NWMI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07112943%2FScreenshot-2023-09-07-at-11.28.4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20draft%20Broadcast%20Bill%20arms%20the%20Union%20government%20with%20disproportionate%20power%20to%20regulate%20India%E2%80%99s%20news%20and%20entertainment%20industries%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnwmindia.org%2Finitiatives%2Fnwmi-reports%2Fthe-proposed-broadcasting-bill-will-irreparably-damage-free-speech-in-india-nwmi%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%2C%20India%20(NWMI)%20has%20warned%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20intent%20to%20do%20this%20will%20%E2%80%9Cirreparably%20damage%20free%20press%2C%20free%20speech%20and%20creative%20freedom%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%2C%20the%20NWMI%20said%20it%20submitted%20a%20%E2%80%9Cclause-by-clause%20analysis%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Bill%20to%20the%20government%20in%20which%20it%20flagged%20issues%20such%20as%20vague%20definitions%2C%20opaque%20regulations%20and%20overriding%20powers%20proposed%20for%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20its%20concerns%20are%20that%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20and%20current%20affairs%20programmes%E2%80%9D%20will%20allow%20it%20to%20regulate%20YouTubers%20and%20citizen%20journalists%2C%20that%20opacity%20around%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20regulations%20would%20prompt%20creators%20to%20%E2%80%9Cavoid%20risk-taking%20at%20all%20costs%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20regime%20proposed%20by%20the%20Bill%20amounted%20to%20the%20government%20%E2%80%9Crunning%20editorial%20panels%20to%20monitor%20content%20being%20generated%20by%20broadcasters%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cautioned%20that%20the%20government%20must%20not%20go%20ahead%20with%20the%20Bill%20without%20exhaustive%20consultations%20with%20stakeholders%20and%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Chaste%20with%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20drafted%20and%20announced%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20the%20limited%20time%20provided%20for%20responses%2C%20is%20unacceptable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1059881%2Fwhy-indias-new-draft-broadcast-bill-has-raised-fears-of-censorship-and-press-suppression%5C%22%3EMedia%20experts%20and%20news%20editors%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20expressed%20their%20concerns%20with%20the%20Bill.%20The%20Editors%E2%80%99%20Guild%20of%20India%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20the%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20framework%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Elaid%20the%20foundations%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Coverarching%20censorship%20framework%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20ministry%20began%20soliciting%20the%20public%E2%80%99s%20feedback%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill%20on%20November%2010%20last%20year.%20The%20last%20date%20for%20providing%20feedback%20was%20December%209.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fparliamentry-announcement%2F2023-12-09%2FDraft_Broadcasting_Services_(Regulation)_Bill%2C_2023.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20text%20of%20the%20draft%20can%20be%20read%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NWMI%E2%80%99s%20full%20statement%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%2C%20India%20(NWMI)%2C%20has%20made%20a%20detailed%20submission%20to%20the%20Central%20Government%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%202023%20that%20was%20published%20by%20the%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20Ministry%20to%20get%20feedback%20from%20the%20public%20and%20all%20stake-holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Broadcasting%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Cable%20Television%20Networks%20(Regulation)%20Act%20of%201995%2C%20with%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20comprehensive%20regulatory%20regime%20for%20all%20forms%20of%20broadcasting%20content%20from%20television%20to%20streaming%20platforms.%20In%20its%20letter%20to%20the%20Ministry%2C%20NWMI%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20government%20bestows%20inordinate%20powers%20on%20itself%20through%20this%20Bill%20to%20control%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20entertainment%20and%20news%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20intent%20to%20control%20and%20over-regulate%20is%20not%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20a%20healthy%2C%20independent%20media%20or%20a%20thriving%20culture%20of%20entertainment.%20It%20goes%20against%20the%20very%20foundations%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20mature%20democracies%20everywhere%20and%20will%20irreparably%20damage%20the%20free%20press%2C%20free%20speech%20and%20creative%20freedom%20in%20India%2C%20NWMI%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20this%20Bill%20could%20potentially%20drastically%20alter%20the%20media%20landscape%20in%20India%2C%20NWMI%20has%20exhorted%20the%20government%20to%20not%2C%20under%20any%20circumstances%2C%20proceed%20with%20it%20without%20exhaustive%20discussions%20among%20the%20key%20stake-holders%20involved.%20Considering%20its%20far-reaching%20implications%2C%20NWMI%20said%20the%20haste%20with%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20drafted%20and%20announced%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20the%20limited%20time%20provided%20for%20responses%2C%20is%20unacceptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20clause-by-clause%20analysis%20submitted%20to%20the%20government%2C%20NWMI%20has%20flagged%20several%20concerns%20that%20are%20summarised%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(1)%20The%20draft%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20vaguely%20worded%20provisions%2C%20including%20its%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnews%20and%20current%20affairs%20programmes%E2%80%9D%2C%20arm%20it%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20cover%20individual%20Youtubers%2C%20the%20social%20media%20accounts%20of%20professional%20journalists%20and%20even%20citizen%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(2)%20The%20Bill%20places%20requirements%20and%20burdens%20on%20news%20organisations%20that%2C%20while%20cumbersome%20for%20large%20broadcasting%20networks%2C%20could%20potentially%20put%20small%20news%20operators%20out%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(3)%20The%20Broadcasting%20Bill%20mentions%20a%20Programme%20Code%20and%20an%20Advertising%20Code%20%E2%80%9Cas%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%9D.%20Any%20public%20consultation%20on%20the%20Bill%20is%20meaningless%20unless%20the%20government%20publishes%20an%20outline%20of%20the%20proposed%20codes%20and%20seeks%20feedback%20on%20those%20codes%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(4)%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20clearly%20defined%20codes%20available%20along%20with%20the%20draft%20Bill%2C%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20draft%20Bill%20in%20itself%20will%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20creators%20of%20entertainment%20and%20news%20content%20who%20will%20be%20driven%2C%20if%20not%20by%20their%20own%20fears%20and%20prevailing%20uncertainty%2C%20then%20by%20the%20management%20of%20their%20organisations%2C%20to%20avoid%20risk-taking%20at%20all%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(5)%20The%20Bill%20shows%20a%20lack%20of%20understanding%20not%20just%20of%20what%20constitutes%20news%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20news%20organisations%20when%20it%20seeks%20to%20club%20them%20with%20creators%20of%20entertainment%20content%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20provision%20to%20subject%20the%20work%20of%20newspersons%20to%20Content%20Evaluation%20Committees%20(CECs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(6)%20The%20Bill%20lays%20out%20a%20system%20of%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20by%20CECs%20that%20are%20to%20be%20constituted%20by%20all%20broadcasters%20and%20broadcasting%20networks%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill.%20However%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cself-certification%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20misnomer%20since%20the%20Bill%20gives%20the%20Central%20Government%20an%20overriding%20role%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20CECs%20and%20amounts%20to%20the%20government%20running%20editorial%20panels%20to%20monitor%20content%20being%20generated%20by%20broadcasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(7)%20The%20Bill%20places%20unreasonable%20curbs%20on%20news%20and%20entertainment%20organisations%20that%20will%20inevitably%20hamper%20their%20functioning%20at%20a%20very%20fundamental%20level%20and%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20make%20it%20financially%20unviable%20for%20small%2C%20independent%20news%20set-ups%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(8)%20In%20the%20context%20of%20OTT%20platforms%2C%20CECs%20look%20set%20to%20mimic%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification%20(CBFC%2C%20known%20in%20popular%20parlance%20as%20the%20Censor%20Board)%2C%20a%20statutory%20body%20that%20has%20been%20criticised%20and%20opposed%20by%20generations%20of%20Indian%20filmmakers.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20bringing%20OTTs%20under%20such%20CBFC-like%20bodies%20defies%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Committee%20of%20Experts%20constituted%20by%20this%20government%20and%20chaired%20by%20the%20renowned%20filmmaker%20Shyam%20Benegal%2C%20that%20had%20called%20for%20a%20more%20liberalised%20certification%20system%20even%20for%20films.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(9)%20The%20Central%20Government%E2%80%99s%20overarching%20role%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20news%20and%20entertainment%20media%20as%20per%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Bill%20is%20further%20enhanced%20by%20the%20requirement%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20Broadcast%20Advisory%20Council%2C%20the%20composition%20of%20which%20will%20primarily%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20Central%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706430042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07112943%2FScreenshot-2023-09-07-at-11.28.4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fintent-to-overregulate-media-behind-draft-broadcast-bill-irreprable-damage-nwmi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vague%20definitions%2C%20opaque%20regulations%20and%20overriding%20powers%20proposed%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20were%20among%20the%20concerns%20the%20NWMI%20said%20it%20flagged%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20while%20providing%20feedback%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fintent-to-overregulate-media-behind-draft-broadcast-bill-irreprable-damage-nwmi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%2