0police%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECatching%20the%20culprits%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20discovering%20the%20pieces%20of%20clothes%20found%20at%20the%20crime%20scene%2C%20Inspector%20Vakatkar%20located%2012%20laundries%20in%20the%20city%20which%20used%20this%20laundry%20mark.%20On%2024%20October%2C%20the%20police%20finally%20zeroed%20in%20on%20the%20American%20Express%20laundry%20at%20Khetwadi%20and%20located%20its%20proprietor%20Shenolikar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20promptly%20told%20the%20PSIs%20Goud%20and%20Dudhat%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98AI%20SBH%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98AI%20Z%E2%80%99%20laundry%20marks%20belonged%20to%20his%20laundry%2C%20and%20the%20two%20male%20customers%20whom%20they%20belonged%20to%20stayed%20in%20the%20same%20locality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20arrests%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20the%20same%20evening%2C%20the%20two%20accused%20Sayed%20Bakar%20Hussain%20and%20Sayed%20Ali%20Asad%20were%20arrested%20at%20Khetwadi%20back%20road.%20The%20two%20confessed%20to%20having%20committed%20the%20crime%20for%20pecuniary%20gain.%20They%20had%20stolen%20cash%2C%20gold%20and%20pearl%20ornaments%20and%20wrist%20watches%20worth%20Rs%2010%2C000.%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fb2jZQOQMCr%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fb2jZQOQMCr%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Dhaval%20Kulkarni%20(%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B2%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A5%80)%20%F0%9F%87%AE%F0%9F%87%B3%20(%40dhavalkulkarni)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdhavalkulkarni%2Fstatus%2F1745164543339474952%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2010%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Dhaval%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20had%20stolen%20cash%2C%20gold%20and%20pearl%20ornaments%2C%20and%20wristwatches%20worth%20Rs%2010%2C000.%20Their%20fingerprints%20tallied%20with%20the%20chance%20prints%20found%20at%20the%20scene%20of%20the%20crime.%20They%20had%20discarded%20the%20blood-stained%20clothes%20and%20worn%20the%20washed%20clothes%20of%20Mr%20Choonawala.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20solve%20any%20crime%2C%20however%2C%20the%20police%20need%20to%20establish%20a%20motive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20police%2C%20Hussain%20was%20Choonawala%E2%80%99s%20driver%20and%20had%20been%20fired%20from%20his%20position.%20Hussain%20believed%20that%20Choonawala%20still%20owed%20him%20dues%20for%20working%20overtime%2C%20etc.%20Choonawala%20argued%20that%20all%20dues%20had%20been%20settled.%20During%20this%20argument%2C%20Hussain%E2%80%99s%20cousin%20Asad%20was%20also%20present.%20The%20argument%20with%20Choonawala%20escalated%20and%20soon%20the%20cousins%20committed%20the%20murder.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20%5Bcousins%5D%20later%20cut%20the%20%3Cem%3Edhobi%3C%2Fem%3E%20mark%20from%20their%20blood-stained%20clothes%20to%20disguise%20their%20identity%2C%20set%20fire%20to%20clothes%2C%20newspapers%2C%20etc%2C%20and%20opened%20the%20gas%20connection%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dhaval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20their%20crimes%2C%20Hussain%20and%20Asad%20were%20sentenced%20to%20death%20by%20a%20principal%20sessions%20judge%20on%204%20November%201968.%20In%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%2C%20the%20police%20had%20nabbed%20the%20culprits%20and%20a%20court%20found%20them%20guilty%20and%20sentenced%20them.%20This%20remarkable%20quadruple%20murder%20case%20was%20among%20the%20last%20cases%20of%20DCP%20Vaidyanath%20Sami%E2%80%99s%20illustrious%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20587px)%20100vw%2C%20587px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FFingerprint-PNG-1705587151.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22587%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Murder%20case%20fingerprints%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FFingerprint-PNG-1705587151.jpg%20587w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FFingerprint-PNG-1705587151-226x300.jpg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FFingerprint-PNG-1705587151-500x664.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FFingerprint-PNG-1705587151-150x199.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-338592%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22780%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFingerprints%20of%20the%20culprits%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20brief%20note%20on%20DCP%20Vaidyanath%20Sami%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20tenure%20in%20the%20Bombay%20Police%2C%20which%20ran%20for%20more%20than%20three%20decades%2C%20DCP%20Vaidyanath%20Someshwar%20Sami%20solved%20many%20mysteries%20in%20ruthless%20criminal%20cases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20however%2C%20he%20had%20never%20imagined%20that%20he%20would%20join%20the%20police%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%2021%20November%2C%201908%2C%20in%20the%20then%20Bombay%2C%20Vaidyanath%20came%20from%20a%20rich%20lineage%20but%20humble%20beginnings.%20Although%20he%20was%20a%20descendent%20of%20Sir%20Kumarapuram%20Sheshadri%20Iyer%2C%20a%20long-time%20Dewan%20of%20Mysore%2C%20his%20father%20Someshwar%20Iyer%20worked%20for%20a%20long%20time%20at%20the%20Bombay%20Tram%20Company%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20then%20Mysore%20where%20he%20endured%20serious%20financial%20difficulties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20his%20family%2C%20Vaidyanath%20went%20to%20find%20work%20in%20Bombay%20after%20graduating%20from%20St%20Joseph%E2%80%99s%20College%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F336383%2Fhomemade-hyderabadi-biryani-in-bengaluru-by-noons-biryani-couple-entrepreneurs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20in%20Bengaluru%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20worked%20odd%20jobs%20as%20a%20screen%20puller%20for%20the%20Opera%20House%20theatre%20and%20an%20insurance%20agent%20before%20he%20joined%20the%20police%20force%20in%201931.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20turning%20point%20in%20his%20career%20came%20in%201939%20when%20he%20was%20made%20part%20of%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20CID.%20This%20was%20done%20by%20senior%20officials%20in%20the%20police%20department%20who%20were%20impressed%20by%20%E2%80%9Chis%20attentive%20and%20dedicated%20work%20ethic%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book%20Jha%20cited%20earlier%20in%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Murder%20case%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMumbai-Murder-Vaidyanath-Sami-1705586304-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-338574%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDCP%20Vaidyanath%20Sami%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20Bombay%20Police%E2%80%99s%20crime%20branch%20for%2028%20years%20and%20retired%20as%20deputy%20commissioner%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20his%20career.%20His%20image%20in%20the%20Bombay%20Police%20was%20that%20of%20an%20impossible%20and%2C%20yet%2C%20intelligent%20officer%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Jha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20an%20investigative%20policeman%20in%20the%20truest%20sense.%20As%20Jha%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20researching%20a%20case%2C%20Sami%20would%20often%20visit%20the%20local%20tea%20shops%20and%20salons%20on%20street%20corners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20believed%20that%20an%20investigation%20was%20like%20hunting%20with%20deep%20patience.%20One%20has%20to%20keep%20one%E2%80%99s%20sixth%20sense%20in%20a%20complete%20state%20of%20alertness.%20During%20the%20quest%2C%20he%20would%20also%20fully%20utilise%20Bombay%20Police%E2%80%99s%20Fingerprint%20Bureau%20and%20the%20Police%20Dog%20Squad.%20He%20placed%20informers%20in%20almost%20all%20the%20colonies%20in%20the%20then%20Bombay%2C%20He%20would%20only%20rest%20once%20he%20had%20enough%20evidence%20against%20the%20accused%20so%20that%20they%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20away%20in%20the%20court%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20it.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20against%20the%20practice%20of%20third-degree%20torture%20of%20criminals%20as%20he%20found%20it%20quite%20inhuman%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20his%20career%2C%20he%20solved%20many%20high-profile%20cases%20including%20the%20Turf%20Soda%20Factory%20murder%20case%2C%20the%20then%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Bank%20robbery%2C%20Lloyd%20Bank%20robbery%20case%2C%20Kuldeep%20murder%20case%2C%20and%20the%20Bombay%20House%20robbery%20case%2C%20amongst%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20would%20find%20clues%20from%20the%20most%20unexpected%20sources%20like%20in%20the%20Bombay%20Lloyds%20Bank%20robbery%20case%2C%20which%20he%20solved%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20clue%20given%20by%20a%20schoolgirl%20or%20an%20unclaimed%20car%20parked%20on%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Road%20in%20the%20then%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Bank%20robbery%20cas